{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-04",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_04_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 4 - The Black Bird",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 6,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 1230.5,
  "page_end_sec": 1473.96,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.737,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 1230.5,
      "end": 1233.024,
      "text": "Will you take care of sending flowers for me?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1233.62,
      "end": 1234.0,
      "text": "I did."
    },
    {
      "start": 1234.912,
      "end": 1236.14,
      "text": "You're an invaluable angel.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1237.12,
      "end": 1238.51,
      "text": "How's your woman's intuition today?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1239.54,
      "end": 1239.8,
      "text": "Why?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1241.1,
      "end": 1242.16,
      "text": "What do you think of Wonderly?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1243.2,
      "end": 1245.62,
      "text": "I'm for her,\" the girl said without hesitation.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1247.0,
      "end": 1248.13,
      "text": "She's got too many names—Wonderly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1249.12,
      "end": 1249.64,
      "text": "LeBlanc,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1249.74,
      "end": 1251.04,
      "text": "and she says the right ones,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1251.08,
      "end": 1251.63,
      "text": "O'Shaughnessy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1252.86,
      "end": 1255.04,
      "text": "I don't care if she's got all the names in the phone book.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1255.6,
      "end": 1256.68,
      "text": "That girl is all right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1256.72,
      "end": 1257.38,
      "text": "and you know it."
    },
    {
      "start": 1257.5,
      "end": 1259.84,
      "text": "I wonder...."
    },
    {
      "start": 1260.704,
      "end": 1262.6,
      "text": "Spade blinked sleepily at Effie Perrine.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1263.34,
      "end": 1263.93,
      "text": "Then he chuckled,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1264.48,
      "end": 1264.88,
      "text": "Anyway,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1265.24,
      "end": 1268.46,
      "text": "she's given up seven hundred bucks in two days and that's all"
    },
    {
      "start": 1268.62,
      "end": 1268.74,
      "text": "right."
    },
    {
      "start": 1270.112,
      "end": 1271.7,
      "text": "Effie Perrine sat up straight and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1272.29,
      "end": 1273.04,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1273.76,
      "end": 1276.98,
      "text": "if that girl's in trouble and you let her down or take advantage"
    },
    {
      "start": 1276.98,
      "end": 1277.96,
      "text": "of it to bleed her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1278.06,
      "end": 1279.44,
      "text": "I'll never forgive you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1279.56,
      "end": 1281.06,
      "text": "never have any respect for"
    },
    {
      "start": 1281.06,
      "end": 1282.24,
      "text": "you as long as I live."
    },
    {
      "start": 1284.36,
      "end": 1285.06,
      "text": "Spade smiled unnaturally.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1286.38,
      "end": 1287.1,
      "text": "Then he frowned.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1288.06,
      "end": 1289.48,
      "text": "The frown also was unnatural.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1290.4,
      "end": 1292.02,
      "text": "He opened his mouth to speak,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1292.14,
      "end": 1294.0,
      "text": "but the sound of someone coming in at the"
    },
    {
      "start": 1294.08,
      "end": 1295.22,
      "text": "corridor door stopped him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1296.192,
      "end": 1297.88,
      "text": "Effie Perrine rose and went into the outer",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1298.0,
      "end": 1298.18,
      "text": "office."
    },
    {
      "start": 1298.79,
      "end": 1301.08,
      "text": "Spade took off his hat and sat in his chair."
    },
    {
      "start": 1302.18,
      "end": 1302.8,
      "text": "The girl returned",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1302.8,
      "end": 1303.5,
      "text": "with a card."
    },
    {
      "start": 1303.66,
      "end": 1304.2,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1304.34,
      "end": 1305.16,
      "text": "Joel Cairo."
    },
    {
      "start": 1306.4,
      "end": 1308.24,
      "text": "\"'This guy is queer,' she said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1309.4,
      "end": 1309.84,
      "text": "\"'In with him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1309.88,
      "end": 1310.06,
      "text": "then,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1310.06,
      "end": 1311.52,
      "text": "darling,' said Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 1313.3,
      "end": 1316.52,
      "text": "Master Joel Cairo was a small-boned dark man of medium height.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1317.34,
      "end": 1318.68,
      "text": "His hair was black and smooth",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1318.9,
      "end": 1319.58,
      "text": "and very glossy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1320.7,
      "end": 1322.1,
      "text": "His features were Levantine.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1322.34,
      "end": 1323.96,
      "text": "A square-cut ruby,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1324.04,
      "end": 1325.46,
      "text": "its sides paralleled by"
    },
    {
      "start": 1325.58,
      "end": 1326.48,
      "text": "four baguette diamonds,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1326.76,
      "end": 1329.1,
      "text": "gleamed against the deep green of his cravat."
    },
    {
      "start": 1330.12,
      "end": 1330.82,
      "text": "His black coat,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1331.02,
      "end": 1332.32,
      "text": "cut tight to narrow shoulders,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1332.6,
      "end": 1334.94,
      "text": "flared a little over slightly plump hips."
    },
    {
      "start": 1336.02,
      "end": 1336.88,
      "text": "His trousers fit",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1336.96,
      "end": 1339.62,
      "text": "his round legs more snugly than was the current fashion."
    },
    {
      "start": 1340.72,
      "end": 1341.9,
      "text": "The uppers of his patent-leather",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1342.0,
      "end": 1343.84,
      "text": "shoes were hidden by fawn spats."
    },
    {
      "start": 1344.23,
      "end": 1347.8,
      "text": "He held a black derby hat in a chamois-gloved hand and came"
    },
    {
      "start": 1347.98,
      "end": 1349.18,
      "text": "toward Spade with short,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1349.36,
      "end": 1349.86,
      "text": "mincing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1349.92,
      "end": 1350.6,
      "text": "bobbing steps."
    },
    {
      "start": 1351.82,
      "end": 1353.76,
      "text": "The fragrance of shebra came with him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1354.72,
      "end": 1357.5,
      "text": "Spade inclined his head at his visitor and then at a chair,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1357.64,
      "end": 1357.88,
      "text": "saying,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1358.688,
      "end": 1358.98,
      "text": "\"'Sit down,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1359.06,
      "end": 1359.2,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1359.3,
      "end": 1362.74,
      "text": "Cairo.' Cairo bowed elaborately over his hat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1362.86,
      "end": 1363.06,
      "text": "said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1364.06,
      "end": 1364.86,
      "text": "\"'I thank you,'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1365.48,
      "end": 1366.28,
      "text": "in a high-pitched,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1366.3,
      "end": 1366.94,
      "text": "thin voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1367.06,
      "end": 1367.8,
      "text": "and sat down."
    },
    {
      "start": 1368.09,
      "end": 1369.98,
      "text": "He sat down primly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1370.44,
      "end": 1371.24,
      "text": "crossing his ankles,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1371.44,
      "end": 1372.76,
      "text": "placing his hat on his knees,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1372.92,
      "end": 1374.7,
      "text": "and began to draw off his yellow gloves."
    },
    {
      "start": 1375.936,
      "end": 1377.64,
      "text": "Spade rocked back in his chair and asked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1378.48,
      "end": 1378.78,
      "text": "\"'Now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1378.88,
      "end": 1379.8,
      "text": "what can I do for you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1379.82,
      "end": 1379.98,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1380.06,
      "end": 1380.46,
      "text": "Cairo?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1381.66,
      "end": 1383.46,
      "text": "The amiable negligence of his tone,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1383.6,
      "end": 1384.94,
      "text": "his motion in the chair,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1385.34,
      "end": 1386.94,
      "text": "were precisely as they had been"
    },
    {
      "start": 1387.14,
      "end": 1389.08,
      "text": "when he had addressed the same question to"
    },
    {
      "start": 1389.08,
      "end": 1391.08,
      "text": "Bridget O'Shaughnessy on the previous day."
    },
    {
      "start": 1392.448,
      "end": 1393.56,
      "text": "Cairo turned his hat over,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1393.68,
      "end": 1394.92,
      "text": "dropped his gloves into it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1394.96,
      "end": 1396.78,
      "text": "and placed it bottom up on the corner"
    },
    {
      "start": 1396.96,
      "end": 1398.08,
      "text": "of the desk nearest him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1399.072,
      "end": 1402.02,
      "text": "Diamonds twinkled on the second and fourth fingers of his left hand,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1402.56,
      "end": 1405.04,
      "text": "a ruby that matched the one in his tie even to"
    },
    {
      "start": 1405.04,
      "end": 1407.08,
      "text": "the surrounding diamonds on the third finger of"
    },
    {
      "start": 1407.08,
      "end": 1407.66,
      "text": "his right hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 1408.74,
      "end": 1410.64,
      "text": "His hands were soft and well cared for.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1411.8,
      "end": 1412.9,
      "text": "Though they were not large,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1413.08,
      "end": 1413.216,
      "text": "their"
    },
    {
      "start": 1413.54,
      "end": 1415.68,
      "text": "flexed bluntness made them seem clumsy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1416.08,
      "end": 1419.2,
      "text": "He rubbed his palms together and said over the whispering"
    },
    {
      "start": 1419.34,
      "end": 1420.06,
      "text": "sound they made,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1420.53,
      "end": 1423.26,
      "text": "May a stranger offer his condolences"
    },
    {
      "start": 1423.26,
      "end": 1425.22,
      "text": "for your partner's unfortunate death?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1425.68,
      "end": 1427.02,
      "text": "\"'Thanks.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1427.744,
      "end": 1428.44,
      "text": "Cairo bowed."
    },
    {
      "start": 1429.824,
      "end": 1430.66,
      "text": "\"'May I ask,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1430.68,
      "end": 1430.88,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1430.92,
      "end": 1431.26,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1431.44,
      "end": 1432.28,
      "text": "if there was,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1432.52,
      "end": 1434.18,
      "text": "as the newspapers inferred,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1434.2,
      "end": 1435.47,
      "text": "a certain—ah—relationship"
    },
    {
      "start": 1437.3,
      "end": 1439.5,
      "text": "between that unfortunate happening and the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1439.5,
      "end": 1441.45,
      "text": "death of a little later of the man Thursby?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 1443.136,
      "end": 1444.96,
      "text": "Spade said nothing in a blank-faced,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1445.12,
      "end": 1445.78,
      "text": "definite way."
    },
    {
      "start": 1446.944,
      "end": 1448.16,
      "text": "Cairo rose and bowed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1449.184,
      "end": 1450.4,
      "text": "\"'I beg your pardon.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1450.75,
      "end": 1454.02,
      "text": "He sat down and placed his hands side by side,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1454.02,
      "end": 1454.84,
      "text": "palms down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1454.98,
      "end": 1456.04,
      "text": "on the corner of the desk."
    },
    {
      "start": 1457.5,
      "end": 1459.68,
      "text": "\"'More than idle curiosity made me ask that,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1459.76,
      "end": 1459.92,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1460.02,
      "end": 1460.28,
      "text": "Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 1460.44,
      "end": 1463.03,
      "text": "I am trying to recover an—a—ornament"
    },
    {
      "start": 1464.8,
      "end": 1465.94,
      "text": "that has been mislaid.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1466.8,
      "end": 1469.568,
      "text": "I thought—I hoped—you could assist me.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1471.072,
      "end": 1473.96,
      "text": "Spade nodded with eyebrows lifted to indicate attentiveness.",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}